INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (64,1,'2023-05-10 17:39:48','2023-05-10 17:39:48','<!-- wp:image {\"id\":65,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://unifacts.local/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/universe2-1024x736.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-65\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>1. Expanding Universe: Unveiling the Unstoppable Stretch of Space</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The universe is constantly expanding. Scientists have observed that galaxies are moving away from each other, indicating that the universe is expanding. This discovery led to the Big Bang theory, which suggests that the universe originated from a hot, dense state and has been expanding ever since.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>2. Black Holes: The Enigmatic Vortexes of Cosmic Conundrums</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Black holes are regions in space where gravity is so strong that nothing, not even light, can escape from them. They form when massive stars collapse under their own gravity. Black holes have a powerful gravitational pull that can distort space and time, making them fascinating objects to study.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":66,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://unifacts.local/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/universe1-1024x640.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-66\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>3. Dark Matter and Dark Energy: Unveiling the Veiled Forces of the Universe</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The majority of the universe is composed of dark matter and dark energy, yet they remain mysterious. Dark matter does not interact with light and other forms of electromagnetic radiation, but its gravitational effects can be observed. Dark energy, on the other hand, is believed to be responsible for the accelerating expansion of the universe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>4. Cosmic Microwave Background Radiation: The Echoes of Creation\'s Birth</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The cosmic microwave background (CMB) radiation is a faint glow of electromagnetic radiation that permeates the entire universe. It is considered to be the remnant heat from the Big Bang. By studying the CMB, scientists gain valuable insights into the early stages of the universe and its evolution.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":67,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://unifacts.local/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/blackHole-1024x461.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-67\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>5. Exoplanets: Peering Beyond Our Solar System\'s Boundaries</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Exoplanets are planets that exist outside our solar system. The discovery of exoplanets has revolutionized our understanding of the universe and the possibility of other habitable worlds. Scientists have identified thousands of exoplanets, some of which may have conditions suitable for life as we know it.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','5 Amazing Facts About the Universe','The Universe','publish','closed','closed','','5-amazing-facts-about-the-universe','','','2023-05-16 21:04:25','2023-05-16 21:04:25','',0,'http://unifacts.local/?p=64',0,'post','',0);
